Preheat your #oven to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Halve any large @broccoli florets{200%g} and pop onto a #baking tray.

Drizzle with @oil{a drizzle}, season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, then toss to coat.

Spread out in a single layer.

When the #oven{} is hot, roast on the top shelf until the edges are crispy and slightly
charred, ~{12-15%minutes}.

In the meantime, bring a large #saucepan of water to the boil with @salt{1/2%tsp} for
the @rigatoni pasta{180%g}.

When boiling, add the rigatoni to the water and bring back to the boil.

Cook until tender, ~{12%minutes}.

Once cooked, drain in a #colander and pop back in the #pan.

Drizzle with @oil{a drizzle} and stir through to stop it sticking together.

While the pasta cooks, peel and grate the @garlic clove{2}(peeled and grated) (or use a
#garlic press{}).

Zest and halve the @lemon{1}(zested and halved).

Heat a drizzle of @oil{a drizzle} in a large #frying pan on medium-high heat.

Once hot, add the lemon zest, @chilli flakes{1%pinch} (add less if you'd prefer things
milder), @breadcrumbs{25%g} and half the garlic.

Season with @salt{} and @pepper{} and fry, stirring regularly, until lightly toasted,
~{3-4%minutes}.

> TIP: Watch it like a hawk as they can burn easily.

Once cooked, transfer the zesty garlic crumb to a #bowl and set aside.

Return the (now empty) #frying pan{} to medium heat with a drizzle of @oil{a drizzle}.

Add the @diced British chicken breast{240%g} and fry until browned all over,
~{5-6%minutes}.

Stir in the remaining garlic and stir-fry for ~{30%seconds}.

Stir in the @creme fraiche{150%g}, @vegetable stock paste{10%g}, @water for the sauce{100%ml}
and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Simmer until thickened slightly, ~{2-3%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash hands and utensils after handling raw meat. Cook so there's no pink
> in the middle.

Stir through the @hard Italian style cheese{20%g}(grated), cooked pasta and
@peas{120%g}.

Simmer until piping hot, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Add a squeeze of @lemon juice{} and stir through.

Taste and add more salt, pepper and lemon juice if needed.

Share the creamy pasta between your bowls and top with the roasted broccoli.

Finish by sprinkling over the zesty garlic crumb.

Enjoy!